name: Fortune Manning
overview:
Fortune Manning is a full service legal firm based in Auckland that provides clients with a range of legal services. It offers its services to a variety of different clients and has experience in working with small businesses through to multi-national businesses and onto individuals and charity organisations.

This legal firm was formed in 1971 when two strong practices merged to become Fortune Manning. With over 100 years of experience Fortune Manning is committed to upholding the value of professional legal advice with a personalized touch. The key market sectors that are focused on by the Fortune Manning team include building, construction, charities, corporate advisory, franchising, insolvency, debt recovery, insurance, international, retirement, transport, trustees, settlors and Beneficiaries.

This firm is well sought after for the experience and extensive knowledge in these sectors. At the base of this firm is a team that is committed to giving full attention to each case and takes care of each client in a personal and professional manner. Fortune Manning proudly holds a number of awards, including the Marsh Insurance Law Award (2006 & 2008), was ASB Mid-Size Law Firm of 2007, and came in as a finalist for many more.
